jnxIfAccountingStats.name: jnxIfAccountingStats

revisions.description: MIB module to define QoS based Interface accounting.
MIB module extended to support inline accounting for Per Forwarding-class stats table for Aggregate (all types of traffic) pkt/byte counters & rate

jnxIfAccountingStats.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net
jnxIfAccountingStats.description: MIB module to define Forwarding Class based Interface statistics. The statistics will provide protocol specific statistics value which includes L2 overhead bytes. The mib is currently supported only on MX platforms.

jnxIfFcAccountStatTable.name: jnxIfFcAccountStatTable
jnxIfFcAccountStatTable.description: This table presents the per forwarding-class and per protocol type statistics.

jnxIfFcAccountStatEntry.name: jnxIfFcAccountStatEntry
jnxIfFcAccountStatEntry.description: This table presents the per forwarding-class and per protocol type statistics. The indices of the table are Interface Index, Forwarding class Index and Protocol type

jnxIfFcFcIndex.name: jnxIfFcFcIndex
jnxIfFcFcIndex.description: The Forwarding Class Index of the interface.

jnxIfFcProtocol.name: jnxIfFcProtocol
jnxIfFcProtocol.description: The protocol type of the entry's traffic.

jnxIfFcHCInUcastPkts.name: jnxIfFcHCInUcastPkts
jnxIfFcHCInUcastPkts.description: The total number of unicast packets ingressed.

jnxIfFcHCInUcastOctets.name: jnxIfFcHCInUcastOctets
jnxIfFcHCInUcastOctets.description: The total number of unicast bytes ingressed.

jnxIfFcHCOutMcastPkts.name: jnxIfFcHCOutMcastPkts
jnxIfFcHCOutMcastPkts.description: The total number of multicast packets egressed.

jnxIfFcInlineAccountingStatTable.name: jnxIfFcInlineAccountingStatTable
jnxIfFcInlineAccountingStatTable.description: This table presents the per forwarding-class and per family statistics without considering the traffic types.

jnxIfFcInlineAccountingStatEntry.name: jnxIfFcInlineAccountingStatEntry
jnxIfFcInlineAccountingStatEntry.description: This table presents the per forwarding-class and per protocol type statistics. The indices of the table are Interface Index, Forwarding class Index and protocol(family) type as defined below.
